<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefaef542-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s3601"><num value="3601">§ 3601.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idefaef543-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s3601/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The term “Agreement” means the International Sugar Agreement, 1977, signed at New York City on <date date="1977-12-09">December 9, 1977</date>.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idefaef544-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s3601/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> The term “sugar” has the same meaning as is given to such term in paragraph (12) of Article 2 of the Agreement.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idefaef545-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s3601/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> The term “entry” means entry, or withdrawal from warehouse, for consumption in the customs territory of the United States.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idefaef546-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/236/s1">Pub. L. 96–236, § 1</ref>, <date date="1980-04-22">Apr. 22, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/336">94 Stat. 336</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
